collectionMetadata.name: Rail Length
collectionMetadata.description: MRT and LRT infrastructure in Singapore (Length of Rail).

datasetMetadata.name: Rail Length (km) At End-of-Year
datasetMetadata.description:
* The MRT network was extended to link Yishun and Chua Chu Kang with the Woodlands Extension in 1996.
* Bukit Panjang LRT started operation in 1999.
* Changi Airport Line commenced operation in 2002.
* North East Line (NEL) and Sengkang LRT opened for service in 2003.
* Punggol LRT opened for service in Jan 2005.
* Boon Lay Extension and Circle Line (CCL) Stage 3 opened for service in Feb and May 2009 respectively.
* CCL Stages 1 & 2 opened for service in Apr 2010.
* CCL Stages 4 & 5 opened for service in Oct 2011.
* Downtown Line (DTL) Stage 1 opened for service in Dec 2013.
* North-South Line Extension opened for service in Nov 2014.
